Asserting that the generic type has an optional property is pretty simple.  Just define an interface that has the property and say that the type extends that interface.  This would look something like

```ts
interface Identifiable {
  id: number;
}

export abstract class BaseRepository&lt;T extends Identifiable&gt; extends Repository&lt;T&gt; {
  async main (changes: DeepPartial&lt;T&gt;) {
    const p = this.create();
    Object.assign(p, changes);

    if (p &amp;&amp; p.id) {
      await this.update(p.id, p);
    }

    const v = await this.save(p);
    return this.findOneOrFail({ where: v })
  }
}
```

